Sad book but loved the way it was written!

Fell in love with this book!!! Last summer I read, “Beach Read” by the same author and this summer I wanted to read another one by her because I already knew she could capture summer and love in such a relaxing but captivating way! Also, a great read of your still trying to figure it all out. 
.
.
.
More in depth (but no spoilers): 
I love when there is a close friend group involved but all the friends are so different from each other. Especially, looks and character wise. Then, of course I love when there’s a red head! There isn’t enough red head characters, so it’s enjoyable when a red head is written and comes to life on page. Makes me feel good because there’s only 2% of us left on the planet lol! 
.
.
.
Secondly, some people know I’m a triplet, but I have never read the word triplet in a book! Reminded me of my family and thought the mention of it in the book was funny. Almost like an inside joke or something because I understand what that’s like and how it roles out over the years. “The Triplets” 😂 
.
.
.
.
Then, I found the part about pockets of women’s pants hilarious! I’m constantly joking how I never have any pockets or a pocket only big enough to squeeze a chapstick in it if I’m lucky. 😂 
.
.
.
.
Of course, I had to also giggle at the mention of cats with the next page I marked. Just read it is all I’m saying. 😂 
.
.
.
.
Lastly, who hasn’t pretended to be a witch ever…and…you know 😂 
.
.
.
.

My weird thoughts/review…⬇️ 🧡
.
.
.
.
.
I have never cried so much but also laughed! I loooooved this book. It kinda makes one comfortable with the unpredictable things in life, especially death. It sounds weird but this book and the characters made me feel like death can also be a funny thing in a way (respectfully) where it’s shocking thing that happens to a human, but where death doesn’t have to be morbid. It can be almost comical because it’s so random. That lessons can be taught out of it where one wasn’t expecting it or needed it. Overall, this book made it seem like it was all going to be okay, no matter what. Hope that makes sense…or I just left the weirdest review but in the best possible way. 😂❤️ #instabook #bookclub #thedeadromantics #ashleyposton #heyashposton
